N:langsmith
D:[langsmith] Instrument, trace, evaluate, and monitor LLM applications with LangSmith. Framework-agnostic: @traceable decorator, wrap_openai/wrap_anthropic wrappers, offline evaluate(), Prompt Hub versioning, feedback attachment, LLM-as-judge with openevals. Supports Python and TypeScript.
G:langsmith langchain tracing observability evaluation llm-monitoring prompt-hub datasets openevals traceable wrap_openai evaluate feedback judge experiment distributed-tracing project

U[8]:
  Add tracing to any LLM pipeline (OpenAI, Anthropic, LangChain, custom models)
  Run offline evaluations with evaluate() against a curated dataset
  Set up production monitoring and online evaluation with real traffic
  Manage and version prompts in the Prompt Hub
  Create datasets for regression testing and benchmarking
  Attach human or automated feedback to traces for quality tracking
  Use LLM-as-judge scoring with openevals (CORRECTNESS_PROMPT, etc.)
  Debug agent failures with end-to-end trace inspection

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Install,pip install -U langsmith (Python) OR npm install langsmith (TypeScript)
  2,Configure,export LANGSMITH_TRACING=true && export LANGSMITH_API_KEY=lsv2_... && export LANGSMITH_PROJECT=my-project
  3,Instrument,@traceable decorator on functions OR wrap_openai(OpenAI()) / wrap_anthropic(Anthropic()) for zero-code-change tracing
  4,Evaluate,results = client.evaluate(target_fn, data="dataset-name", evaluators=[fn], experiment_prefix="v1", max_concurrency=4)
  5,Monitor,view traces at smith.langchain.com; attach feedback with client.create_feedback(key="correctness", score=1, run_id=id)

R[5]:
  Always set LANGSMITH_PROJECT to group related traces by feature/environment
  Use wrap_openai/wrap_anthropic for zero-code-change tracing of provider clients
  For distributed tracing across microservices pass run_tree.to_headers() between services
  For LLM-as-judge use openevals create_llm_as_judge with CORRECTNESS_PROMPT or custom prompts
  Use tracing_context(enabled=False) block to selectively disable tracing for specific sections

E[4]{type,code}:
  Trace Python function,@traceable(run_type="chain", tags=["prod"]) def fn(): ...
  Wrap OpenAI client,client = wrap_openai(OpenAI())  # all calls auto-traced
  Run evaluation,results = client.evaluate(target, data="Geography QA", evaluators=[exact_match])
  LLM-as-judge,judge = create_llm_as_judge(prompt=CORRECTNESS_PROMPT, model="openai:o3-mini", feedback_key="correctness")
